<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-09-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-09-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="858" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d858">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to Ambassador <persName type="to">Meyer</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-09-22"><hi rend="italic">September 22,
                                    1905</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Adee instructs Mr. Meyer to inform the Russian Government that the
                            Japanese Government intends to carry out the arrangement for the
                            exchange of prisoners soon after the ratification of the treaty by the
                            respective sovereigns, and that in this respect the treaty will operate
                            even before the exchange of the ratifications.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>